<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-12-01T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-12-01T18:00:00-05:00" n="380" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d380">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">125.199/58: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Consul at Seville</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bay</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-12-01T18:00:00-05:00">December 1, 1937—6
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your November 20, 9 a.m. In view of continued delay in granting of safe
                            conduct for Chapman’s return to Bilbao, he has been authorized to return
                            to the United States on leave, unless before his departure, probably
                            within a week, such permit is granted. Please report as soon as possible
                            result of action promised by General Queipo de Llano.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>